result.execSummary:
The defendant Ryan Justin Webster was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Ryan Justin Webster is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Ryan Justin Webster was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: MARQUETTE  COUNTY DNA PROOF OF SUBMISSION

Defendant Ryan Justin Webster in court with attorney Brian Severson.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states plea agreement.  Defendant to enter plea to Ct 2.  State will move to dismiss Ct 1.  Atty Severson agrees.  Defendant enters No Contest plea to Ct 2.  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  Court questions Atty Severson.  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct 2.  Count 1 is ordered dismissed.
Counsel make sentencing arguments.
BY THE COURT:  Sentence withheld, defendant placed on probation for a period of 12 months with the following conditions:  *Pay costs of $243.00.  *Submit DNA sample and pay surcharges of $200.00.  *Counseling as recommended by the agent.  *Granted 11 days credit if probation is revoked.  *Bond on file to be applied and any balance returned.

State files Information.  Atty Severson received the Information and waives the reading.  Not guilty plea entered.
BY THE COURT:  Set for return.  Bond continued.

Defendant Ryan Justin Webster in court with attorney Brian Severson.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant waives his right to a preliminary hearing.  Court questions defendant and finds his waiver to be made freely, voluntarily and intelligently.  BY THE COURT:  Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and this defendant committed it.  Case bound over for trial or further proceedings.  Return date scheduled for January 20, 2016 at 02:30 pm.

Defendant Ryan Justin Webster in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
 Atty Gumz states that the Defendant received a copy of the criminal complaint & waives it's reading.  Atty Gumz waives time limits for the Prelim.

BY THE COURT: Time limits waived; Set for Prelim.
bond continued.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for November 4, 2015 at 10:00 am.
letter from defendant and response from Court

Defendant Ryan Justin Webster in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Defendant Ryan Justin Webster in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that the defendant just received the criminal complaint.  Atty Gumz asks for this to be just a bond hearing as he has not seen the complaint yet.
Atty Hendee requests a $500 cash bond with conditions due to the defendant is out on bond from Washington county.
Atty Gumz responds.

BY THE COURT:  Court sets a $500 cash bond with conditions:
*Absolute Sobriety; zero tolerance  Initial appearance scheduled for September 14, 2015 at 02:30 pm.
